The paper proposes a visual approach to understand and analyze the flow of information in a machine learning system. The use of Sankey diagrams is a visualization technique that is commonly used to understand data flow among sets. The paper focuses on the analysis of training data, features, and classifier performance, which are all related to machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
